Dear Colleagues,
   a new book on higher category theory has just appeared with Springer:
S. Paoli, Simplicial Methods for Higher Categories: Segal-Type Models of We=
ak n-Categories, Algebra and Applications 26, Springer 2019
https://www.springer.com/gb/book/9783030056735<https://eur03.safelinks.prot=
ection.outlook.com/?url=3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.springer.com%2Fgb%2Fbook%2F9783=
030056735&data=3D02%7C01%7Csp424%40leicester.ac.uk%7Ce869b44f0316479a65db08=
d6f8a9bfd7%7Caebecd6a31d44b0195ce8274afe853d9%7C0%7C0%7C636969805281563989&=
sdata=3D08lejPwWXU2Yc86EpYrkPLHiWeocARAeLnMfw5%2F%2F1hs%3D&reserved=3D0>
This is a research monograph introducing a new model of higher categories, =
called weakly globular n-fold categories, and proving its equivalence with =
the Tamsamani-Simpson model. The book also contains an introduction to high=
er category theory and a detailed background chapter on multi-simplicial te=
chniques, rendering the material relatively self-contained and accessible t=
o researchers entering the area.  I hope the book will be of interest both =
to category theorists and algebraic topologists.
Best wishes,
Simona.
Dr Simona Paoli, Department of Mathematics, University of Leicester (UK)



